TY  - JOUR
AU  - Doshi, Hitesh
AU  - Elkamhi, Redouane
AU  - Simutin, Mikhail
T1  - Managerial Activeness and Mutual Fund Performance
PY  - 2015
Y1  - 2015/12/01
DO  - 10.1093/rapstu/rav005
JO  - The Review of Asset Pricing Studies
JA  - Rev Asset Pric Stud
VL  - 5
IS  - 2
SP  - 156
EP  - 184
SN  - 2045-9920
AB  - A closet indexer is more likely to meet a value-weighted investment benchmark by value weighting the portfolio. Following this intuition, we introduce a simple measure of active management, the absolute difference between the value weights and actual weights held by a fund, summed across its holdings. This proxy captures managerial skill: active funds outperform passive ones by 2.5% annually. Compared with known measures of skill, our proxy robustly predicts fund flows, asset growth, factor-adjusted performance, and value added. Its predictive ability is orthogonal to that of other measures and is robust to controlling for volatility timing, past performance, and style. (JEL G10, G12, G14, G20, G23)
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rapstu/rav005
ER  - 



